bug.short_desc: NetworkManager cannot connect to wifi after 4.8.x --> 4.9.x upgrade
bug.cf_doc_type: If docs needed, set a value

long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 1248818 content of: journalctl -f -n 0 | tee connection.log while NM tries to connect
Description of problem:
After upgrading my netbook from 4.8.x kernel to 4.9.x series, NetworkManager cannot connect any longer...I'm including the log file. Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable):
How reproducible:
Steps to Reproduce: 1. 2. 3.
Actual results:
Expected results:
Additional info:
$ dmesg | grep rtl8192 16.338693] rtl8192ce: Using firmware rtlwifi/rtl8192cfw.bin [ 18.020950] rtl8192ce 0000:01:00.0 wlp1s0: renamed from wlan0
snippet from lspci -k:
01:00.0 Network controller: Realtek Semiconductor Co., Ltd. RTL8188CE 802.11b/g/n WiFi Adapter (rev 01) Subsystem: Realtek Semiconductor Co., Ltd. Device 8195 Kernel driver in use: rtl8192ce Kernel modules: rtl8192ce

Forgot to add that NM does not properly populate
/etc/resolv.conf
since there is no longer:
nameserver w.x.y.z
entry.
Can you test on a rawhide kernel? The maintainers mentioned there was a fix https://git.kernel.org/cgit/linux/kernel/git/torvalds/linux.git/commit/?id=52f5631a4c05 that might cause problems
Tried with 4.10.0-0.rc7.git3.1.fc26 kernel and it does work!
Confirming Saša's observation: Installing kernel-4.10.0-0.rc8.git2.1.fc26 from https://koji.fedoraproject.org/koji/packageinfo?packageID=8 made the problem go away.
This fix is now in stable releases. Thanks for reporting and testing.
